      <preamble>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Regulations in exercise of the powers conferred by section 31(2) of the Islands (Scotland) Act 2018<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/>.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>These Regulations may be cited as the Islands (Scotland) Act 2018 (Commencement No. 2) Regulations 2019 and come into force on 18 April 2019.</p>
            </content>
         </hcontainer>
         <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-2">
            <heading>Appointed day</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
               <p>The day appointed for the coming into force of section 11(2) (guidance about section 7 duty) and the schedule (duties in relation to island communities: relevant authorities) of the Islands (Scotland) Act 2018 is 18 April 2019.</p>
            </content>
         </hcontainer>
